org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.scopes

Class LargeDefinitionStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap<String,IDefinitionSet>
        • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.scopes.LargeDefinitionStore
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Map<String,IDefinitionSet>, IDefinitionStore

    public final class LargeDefinitionStore
extends HashMap<String,IDefinitionSet>
implements IDefinitionStore
    An implementation of IDefinitionStore for large numbers of definitions.

    This implementation extends HashMap, instead of having a HashMap, in order to save memory. The keys of the map are the base names of the definitions. The values of the map are definition sets containing definitions with the same base name.

    See Also:

      • createLargerStore

        public IDefinitionStore createLargerStore()
        Description copied from interface: IDefinitionStore
        Creates another definition store with a greater capacity.

        When a call to IDefinitionStore.add(org.apache.flex.compiler.definitions.IDefinition)() on this store returns false (because the store has reached its capacity), call this method to create a larger store and then call add()) on it. The second add() is guaranteed to succeed.

        Specified by:
        createLargerStore in interface IDefinitionStore
        Returns:
        An IDefinitionStore with a greater capacity.
